Londen Walt & will Kent
sence mij last of 13 cur rec yours of 20, 24 & 27 past with
actt & patt of N37 aboard geerd hendrickx for Rott which
pray god send well, butt non of my cullours yett, so that N36
&37 are to little purpose, more blew grayer then I ordered &
non ofo the cullours of N4& 3 of 18 march the chest mixt
cullours must be as by the inclosed, of which I would have of all
prises a pis viz one of 6,1 of 6:6 one of 7 p of 8 one of 4
one of 10 2 of 13 a 14 ƒ & one of 15 p I say upon these goound
close & small mixture & one if to be had of this ground
mixt with white & blew like a drap butt as das & little
micture as possible of 13: 14 a 15 s & further exspect
the patt of clothes now most demanded as writt by my formars
I will have no H½½ y allow marks att £100: the 10 p
hope you shall finde the EE mixt & you may add1 of 2p
whites for atryall of the qualitie of the yallow for you
writt mee before hope the bayes kersies & cloth to come ptt
first convoy for amst. att least one pack of kersies as writt
refore, in closed a letter of my good freind m Ab gansackes
to which your answer p first, I rest
